{FilenameWithExtension}: "Time With" a leader and other/younger teens.
{Name}: "Time With" a leader and other/younger teens.
Description:
Examples: Ice Cream outing, movies, camping trip.

3 times a month. Spend significant time with other teens with the supervision of a TFC Staff member. This will help to teach this student how to love on peers.
Title: "Time With" a leader and other/younger teens.

{FilenameWithExtension}: Present the Gospel
{Name}: Present the Gospel
Description: Give a Gospel presentation to the student when they are ready and repentant.
Title: Present the Gospel

{FilenameWithExtension}: Share scripture with them
{Name}: Share scripture with them
Description:
Examples: Something you're learning. Something you think would be encouraging to them.

Do this once week for at least a month or two. When they are Responsive, Ready, or Repentant.
Title: Share scripture with them

{FilenameWithExtension}: Pray for them weekly
{Name}: Pray for them weekly
Description: Examples: To become aware of God's love. Receptive to the Gospel. Curious about Jesus. Attentive to the Word.
Title: Pray for them weekly

{FilenameWithExtension}: Follow up from presenting the Gospel
{Name}: Follow up from presenting the Gospel
Description:
Example: "33 things that happen at Salvation Booklet"
Find out what they understand and how it should be changing them.
Title: Follow up from presenting the Gospel

{FilenameWithExtension}: Be their friend them in at least 3 ways this week
{Name}: Be their friend them in at least 3 ways this week
Description:
Examples: Start a non-religious conversation with them. Sit with them at a meal. Encourage them on something they've done or are in. Send them a text telling them they did good at a ballgame.
This is an ongoing task.
Title: Be their friend them in at least 3 ways this week

{FilenameWithExtension}: Invite them to join you doing something
{Name}: Invite them to join you doing something
Description: Examples: Build something or fix something. Getting groceries. Play disk golf. Coffee/Coke.
Title: Invite them to join you doing something

{FilenameWithExtension}: Pray with them
{Name}: Pray with them
Description: Examples: Pray with them on their birthdays. Pray with them when something hard is going on.
Title: Pray with them

{FilenameWithExtension}: Go through Disciplemaker Living Guide with someone in Chair 3
{Name}: Go through Disciplemaker Living Guide with someone in Chair 3
Title: Go through Disciplemaker Living Guide with someone in Chair 3

{FilenameWithExtension}: Send a note of encouragement or text saying what you see in them
{Name}: Send a note of encouragement or text saying what you see in them
Description: Show them that they matter and help them to see how God sees them.
Title: Send a note of encouragement or text saying what you see in them

{FilenameWithExtension}: Go through One Another Living Guide with someone in Chair 3
{Name}: Go through One Another Living Guide with someone in Chair 3
Title: Go through One Another Living Guide with someone in Chair 3

{FilenameWithExtension}: Go on a Mission Trip
{Name}: Go on a Mission Trip
Description: Inviting them to be on a mission trip will help them to make a lot of good "walking" choices and teach them how Christians live day in and day out.
Title: Go on a Mission Trip

{FilenameWithExtension}: Devo leader in training at Camp
{Name}: Devo leader in training at Camp
Description: Inviting them to teach others is a great step at understanding that our faith is one to be shared and that others are incredibly important to Jesus.
Title: Devo leader in training at Camp

{FilenameWithExtension}: Go through John 3:16 Living Guide with someone in Chair 3
{Name}: Go through John 3:16 Living Guide with someone in Chair 3
Title: Go through John 3:16 Living Guide with someone in Chair 3

{FilenameWithExtension}: Personal Bible Reading Plan
{Name}: Personal Bible Reading Plan
Description: Teaching them to feed themselves by reading scripture on their own is one of the most vital skills. Be ready to encourage them and check in with them over and over with this task. It is likely to be ongoing and one to pray for constantly.
Title: Personal Bible Reading Plan

{FilenameWithExtension}: Bible study with a Leader
{Name}: Bible study with a Leader
Description: Doing a Bible study with you or another leader will help them to see HOW to read scripture. Since the Bible is such an old and complicated book, we forget that it is an acquired taste to be read.
Title: Bible study with a Leader

{FilenameWithExtension}: Ministry Team
{Name}: Ministry Team
Description: Inviting them to begin to lead forces teens to dive deeper. In order to help and lead others, they have to know their stuff. Ask them to step up.
Title: Ministry Team

{FilenameWithExtension}: Disciplemaking Is Relationships Training
{Name}: Disciplemaking Is Relationships Training
Title: Disciplemaking Is Relationships Training

{FilenameWithExtension}: Disciplemaker Living Guide with someone in Chair 2/3
{Name}: Disciplemaker Living Guide with someone in Chair 2/3
Title: Disciplemaker Living Guide with someone in Chair 2/3

{FilenameWithExtension}: Ministry is Relationships Training
{Name}: Ministry is Relationships Training
Title: Ministry is Relationships Training

{FilenameWithExtension}: One Another Living guide with someone in Chair 2/3,
{Name}: One Another Living guide with someone in Chair 2/3,
Description: The One Another Living guide is to help teens in chairs 2 and 3 to be able to share life well with their peers who are in chair 1 and the beginning stages of chair 2. The idea is mostly that they are a witness by the way they live. This guide assists them in understanding how to do that.
Title: One Another Living guide with someone in Chair 2/3,

{FilenameWithExtension}: Devo Leader at Camp
{Name}: Devo Leader at Camp
Description: Devo leaders at camp are one of the greatest places to learn to walk more like Jesus. Continue to encourage them to do this each year!
Title: Devo Leader at Camp

{FilenameWithExtension}: Ministry Team
{Name}: Ministry Team
Description: If they aren't on Ministry Team, get them there. As someone in chair 3 they should be sharing with others how walking like Christ is!
Title: Ministry Team

{FilenameWithExtension}: Evangelism is Relationships Training
{Name}: Evangelism is Relationships Training
Description: This training will help teens know how to share Jesus in the context of relationships.
Title: Evangelism is Relationships Training

{FilenameWithExtension}: John 3:16 Living Guide with someone in Chair 2/3
{Name}: John 3:16 Living Guide with someone in Chair 2/3
Description: This guide is for those in chair 2 and 3 to teach them how to share with peers in chair 1 and the beginning stages of chair 3.
Title: John 3:16 Living Guide with someone in Chair 2/3

{FilenameWithExtension}: Choose 3 people to pray for specifically
{Name}: Choose 3 people to pray for specifically
Description: As someone in chair 3 they should be consistently praying for their peers. Encourage them and check in with them weekly so this becomes a habit.
Title: Choose 3 people to pray for specifically
